# SG Couture — Cursor wiring

`AGENTS.md` and `CLAUDE.md` are the source of truth. This rule only wires Cursor-specific habits.

## Before coding

1. Read `docs/DEVELOPMENT_PHASES.md` and identify the active phase + acceptance criteria.
2. Use the docs map in `AGENTS.md` — read only the docs relevant to the task.
3. Do not invent business logic absent from `docs/FEATURES.md`. Ask, then document, then implement.

## Agents (when available)

| Agent | When |
|---|---|
| `docs-explorer` | Library/framework docs before implementing against something unfamiliar |
| `fable-advisor` | Architecture decision, schema migration, or refactor touching 3+ files — treat Flag as blocking |
| `phase-guard` | Before starting implementation and before declaring a task done |
| `api-documenter` | After adding/changing controller routes — check API-spec drift |

## Skills (use by name)

- Endpoints: `new-endpoint`, `nestjs-swagger`
- NestJS / Prisma: `nestjs-patterns`, `prisma-patterns`
- Quality: `test-patterns`, `tdd-workflow`, `clean-typescript`, `security-review`
- Done: `task-close` (mandatory checklist before saying a task is finished)

## Tooling

- Package manager: **pnpm** only (never npm/yarn).
